Description: Fragment of a plaster jar-sealing. The inner concave surface bears part of a negative impression of a cartouche of a king Psamtek; the outer convex surface bears a positive impression of another cartouche, possibly the same one. The sealing should have belonged to a second layer of plaster which was covering a first layer already stamped with a cartouche (see EA 23791 coming from the same findspot). The cartouche is vertical and surmounted by a solar disc between two ostrich feathers.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 8, west of the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 8 has been scratched into the object. See London, BM, EA 23791 coming from the same findspot (8) and showing the same stamp as originally impressed on a first layer of plaster on the neck of the sealed pottery. See also Bolton, 1886.28.112.
